ook. When viewed, this content automatically displays links to adjacent book pages, providing a simple navigation system for creating and reviewing structured content.','','none'),(3249,'','default','The outline feature allows you to include pages in the <a href=\"@book\">Book hierarchy</a>, as well as move them within the hierarchy or to <a href=\"@book-admin\">reorder an entire book</a>.','','none'),(3250,'','default','Create new books','','none'),(3251,'','default','Add content and child pages to books','','none'),(3252,'','default','View printer-friendly books','','none'),(3253,'','default','View a book page and all of its sub-pages as a single document for ease of printing. Can be performance heavy.','','none'),(3254,'','default','<em>Books</em> have a built-in hierarchical navigation. Use for handbooks or tutorials.','','none'),(3255,'','default','Allows users to create and organize related content in an outline.','','none'),(3256,'','default','The Color module allows users with the <em>Administer site configuration</em> permission to quickly and easily change the color scheme of themes that have been built to be compatible with it. For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@color\">Color module</a>.','','none'),(3257,'','default','Changing colors','','none'),(3258,'','default','Using the Color module allows you to easily change the color of links, backgrounds, text, and other theme elements. To change the color settings for a compatible theme, select the <em>Settings</em> link for your theme on the <a href=\'@configure\'>Themes administration page</a>. If you don\'t see a color picker on that page, then your theme is not compatible with the color module. If you are sure that the theme does indeed support the color module, but the color picker does not appear, then <a href=\'@troubleshoot\'>follow these troubleshooting procedures</a>.','','none'),(3259,'','default','The Color module saves a modified copy of the theme\'s specified styles